# Website Conversion/Cloning: `src/app` Page Structure

When converting or cloning a website, preserve this page-routing structure:

- `src/app/` contains the site's URL structure.
- Each subfolder maps directly to a URL path.

Examples:

- `src/app/page.tsx` -> homepage (`/`)
- `src/app/about/page.tsx` -> about page (`/about`)
- `src/app/services/[slug]/page.tsx` -> service pages (`/services/ac-repair`, etc.)
- `src/app/service-areas/[slug]/page.tsx` -> city/location pages (`/service-areas/houston`, etc.)
- `src/app/contact/page.tsx` -> contact page (`/contact`)

Note on dynamic routes:

- `[slug]` folders are dynamic routes.
- A single `[slug]/page.tsx` can generate hundreds of pages.
- Content for each generated page comes from PMS data.
